commText: KKR are through. They win by 18 runs and remain on 18 points with 2 (away) games to go. As for MI, they will play LSG at home next week and would hope to end the season on a high. In action from a few hours from now will be 4 teams that are well and truly in contention for the playoffs. It also marks the penultimate double-header clash of the season. Going to be an absolute cracker folks. Do remember to join us for all the fun. Until next time, good night and goodbye from I0$ and I1$. Cheers!!

Varun Chakaravarthy | Player of the Match: The plan was to make him (Rohit) hit across the line, obviously there was help from the wicket and I was able to use it to my advantage. Tactically we (talking about Narine) are similar, but technically we are slightly different. The wickets were too flat initially, my bowling has been same from the first match and it is just that the results are showing up now.

Shreyas Iyer | KKR skipper: I think I manifested this before the game (on becoming the 1st side to qualifty for the playoffs). Nerves were there, boys have been raising their hands and there have been many game-changers and kudos to each and every one of them. I feel whichever team plays the best, they got a great chance to win. They were going at great guns in the first 6 overs, and to bounce back from that situation it was nice to see. I wasn't thinking about stats or records, the weather wasn't great but we won the game and that's what is more important. It's all about understanding which bowler is doing well on that particular day, I feel both of them bowled well and my gut went with Varun (on bowling the 4th over) at that point and I backed him.
400 runs and 15 wickets in an IPL edition (472, 17) - Shane Watson (RR, 2008) (409, 15) - Jacques Kallis (KKR, 2012) (461, 15) - Sunil Narine (KKR, 2024)
Most wins for a team at a venue (IPL): 52 - KKR (Kolkata) 52 - MI (Mumbai WS) 49 - CSK (Chennai) 42 - RCB (Bengaluru) 37 - RR (Jaipur) *including Super Over results
Most wins for KKR at the Eden Gardens in an IPL edition: 5 out of 7 (2010) 5 out of 6 (2015) 5 out of 9 (2018) 5 out of 7 (2024) (They had won 4 out of 4 in 2014)
Most defeats for MI in an IPL season: 10 - 2022 9* - 2024 8 - 2009 8 - 2014 8 - 2018
This is the first time KKR have beaten MI both at Wankhede and at the Eden Gardens in an IPL season.
550 or more wickets in Men’s T20 cricket: 625 - Dwayne Bravo 574 - Rashid Khan 550 - Sunil Narine
Pace vs spin in MI’s innings \nSpin: 3/38 from 7 overs (ER: 5.42) \nPace: 4/95 from 9 overs (ER: 10.55)

Andre Russell: We batted first, so we knew it (pitch) was a bit sticky and something in it for the spinners as well. Based on our bowling attack we felt that was good enough. They got off to a good start, we pulled it back brilliantly. Our bowlers won it for us. He (SKY) is a 360 guy. I tried to keep it as simple as possible. I think it's just about belief. The older you get the more experience you get. Have worked on my fitness and happy to do whatever the team needs. I have been doing as much talking as I can (to the team). We have a lot of youngsters. Everyone wants to do well. They listen to all the experienced guys and they are willing to learn.

Hardik Pandya | MI Captain: Tough one, yeah. As a batting unit, the foundation was there but we could not capitalize after that and keep the momentum up. The wicket was a little up and down and a little tacky so momentum was very important. I think it was a par score, given the conditions, felt that the bowlers did well. Every ball that came back from the boundary came back wet. The bowlers made sure they kept taking wickets. (On his thoughts for the next game) Nothing, just to go and enjoy as much as we can and play good cricket, that’s been my motto from the start. I don’t think we’ve played enough good cricket this season.

00:33 local, 19:03 GMT: To summarize the chase. KKR pacers = 95/4 in 9 overs. Their spin-duo = 38/3 in 7 overs. At the end of 5 overs, MI were 59/0 and seemed firm favourites to complete the target. However, 6 overs of spin outside the powerplay turned things upside down for the visitors. Rohit struggled to connect a few and most of the MI batters found it tough to get going against spin due to the sticky nature of the surface. Tilak tried his best, but there was just too much to do at the end despite a breezy 6-ball 17 cameo from Dhir. All in all, KKR manage a much-needed win and given their high-flying NRR, it is highly likely that they might well finish in the top 2. Stick around for the post-match reactions...

Harshit Rana to Anshul Kamboj, 1 run, chipped away to mid-wicket, but it won't matter one bit for KKR. They become the first side to qualify to the playoffs and continue to rule roost at the top of the table. They win by 18 runs and finish their home leg on a high
Harshit Rana to Chawla, 1 run, length delivery bowled at I0$ outside off, chopped away to backward point
Harshit Rana to Chawla, no run, bumper slanting away outside off, Chawla hops and looks to ramp it over the keeper. No dice...
Piyush Chawla, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Harshit Rana to Tilak Varma, out Caught by Philip Salt!! That's the game for KKR and they can start celebrating their playoff spot as well. Harshit Rana dragged the length back and kept it well wide of the arc outside off, Tilak Varma was all hands trying to slash it over covers and gets a healthy outside edge through to the keeper. Tilak Varma c Philip Salt b Harshit Rana 32(17) [4s-5 6s-1]
Harshit Rana to Tilak Varma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
21 needed from 4
Harshit Rana to Anshul Kamboj, 1 run, Kamboj looks to hit leg-side and gets an inside edge onto pad for a single
Anshul Kamboj, right handed bat, comes to the crease
22 needed from 5

Harshit Rana to Naman Dhir, out Caught by Rinku Singh!! Harshit Rana is chuffed to bits. Naman Dhir has been caught at deep mid-wicket. He moves a long way across off and tries to pull the short delivery on the leg-side, gets it off the thick top-edge and Rinku takes a fine catch running across to his right in the deep. Naman Dhir c Rinku Singh b Harshit Rana 17(6) [4s-1 6s-2]
Harshit Rana to Naman Dhir, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
MI need 22 from 6

Russell to Naman Dhir, 1 run, Russell goes short outside off, Dhir looks to help it with a pull and the top-edge flies to the right of the keeper. Salt was too eager to get there and trips over while trying to dive. Had he not slipped, that would have been a relatively easy opportunity for the KKR keeper...
23 needed from 7
Russell to Naman Dhir, FOUR, one bounce and over the ropes! Russell goes full and wide of off, Dhir stays deep inside the crease and carves it up and over extra cover with terrific timing
27 needed from 8
Russell to Naman Dhir, SIX, Russell misses the yorker and serves another low full toss outside off, Dhir clears his front leg and marmalizes it for an 80-metre maximum over mid-wicket

Russell to Naman Dhir, no run, I0$ yorker pinged in the blockhole outside off, Naman Dhir looks to slice it behind square on the off-side but gets inside edge onto boot. Tilak Varma wanted a quick single, but sent back!
Russell to Naman Dhir, SIX, low full toss on the stumps, Naman Dhir crouches and swats it for a 71-metre maximum over deep square with an air of nonchalance
Russell to Tilak Varma, 1 run, yorker length wide of off at I0$, Tilak toe-ends the drive to the right of extra cover
Russell to Tilak Varma, wide, bumper outside off. Tilak looks to pull and misses. Called wide for height...
Naman Dhir, right handed bat, comes to the crease
41 needed off the last 2 overs

Harshit Rana to Nehal Wadhera, out Nehal Wadhera Run Out!! 1 run completed. Nehal Wadhera wasn't even in the frame. He went on the back foot and slapped the length delivery down the ground to the left of long-off. There was never a two there, but Tilak Varma wanted to take a chance and keep strike. Starc though was smart enough to understand the plan and threw at the right end to catch the batter well short of his crease. Nehal Wadhera run out (Starc/Philip Salt) 3(3)
Harshit Rana to Nehal Wadhera, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!
Harshit Rana to Tilak Varma, 1 run, back of a length wide of off, Tilak slogs and loses shape in the process. Dragged off the thick inside edge to the left of deep mid-wicket
Harshit Rana to Tilak Varma, FOUR, slower length delivery bowled at I0$ outside off, Tilak Varma switched his stance and swatted it away in the gap to the right of short third
Harshit Rana to Tilak Varma, no run, another slower delivery, Tilak Varma drags it from outside off to the left of the bowler

Harshit Rana to Tilak Varma, SIX, another slower ball dished wide of off, Tilak Varma heaves the pull and manages enough contact to beat both the fielders in the deep on the leg-side (deep mid-wicket and long-on)
Harshit Rana to Tilak Varma, FOUR, full and wide of off. It was the slower ball, but Tilak Varma picked it and slogged it away behind square on the leg-side
Harshit Rana [1.0-0-15-0] is back into the attack
MI need 57 off the last 3 overs
Russell to Tilak Varma, 1 run, I0$ yorker length wide of off, Tilak jams it towards backward point for a quick single
Russell to Nehal Wadhera, 1 run, slower short ball outside off, Nehal Wadhera is early into the drive/cut and gets a thick top-edge that lands wide of cover to his right
Russell to Tilak Varma, 1 run, slower short ball outside off, Tilak Varma makes room and mistimes the drive to the right of sweeper cover

Russell to Tilak Varma, FOUR, Ramandeep drops a tough one. Tilak Varma muscles the short ball to the left of deep mid-wicket and Ramandeep does splendidly well to run a lot of ground to his left in the deep. Got there in time but couldn't gather the ball cleanly at the last second....
Russell to Nehal Wadhera, 1 run, I0$ banged in short down leg, Nehal Wadhera pulls and gets it off the toe that teases Salt to his right on his attempted leap
Russell to Nehal Wadhera, wide, bumper angling away outside off, Nehal Wadhera looks to pull and gets beaten by the extra bounce
Nehal Wadhera, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Russell to Tim David, out Caught by Shreyas Iyer!! The wheels are coming off for MI. Russell takes the pace off and bowls it short outside off, Tim David goes for the heave-ho and fails to find the middle of the bat. Off the inside half and Shreyas takes a fine catch running forward from deep mid-wicket, Tim David c Shreyas Iyer b Russell 0(3)
Russell to Tim David, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Chakaravarthy to Tim David, leg byes, 1 run, looks to block off the back foot and gets surprised by the extra bounce on that. Rolls off the splice wide of backward point for a quick single
Chakaravarthy to Tim David, no run, defends hurriedly into the off-side
Tim David, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Chakaravarthy to Hardik Pandya, out Caught by Vaibhav Arora!! Chakaravarthy gets another crucial wicket and no wonder he's been given the 4th over. Goes short outside off, it sticks up on the surface as Hardik Pandya tries to slog leg-side. A thick leading edge and offers catching practice to the fielder at backward point to his left. Hardik Pandya c Vaibhav Arora b Chakaravarthy 2(4)
Chakaravarthy to Hardik Pandya, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Chakaravarthy to Tilak Varma, 1 run, fuller on the stumps, driven down to long-on
Chakaravarthy to Tilak Varma, wide, tad fuller and wider of off stump, Tilak looks to sweep and misses. Past the guide line and signalled a wide
Chakaravarthy to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, short outside off, Hardik heaves the pull to the right of deep mid-wicket
Chakaravarthy to Hardik Pandya, no run, quicker and straighter from Varun, Hardik stabs it into the off-side
Summary (Overs 6-11) > Kishan becomes the first to fall > Rohit struggles and gets out the very next over > Narine and Chakaravarthy keep it tight > SKY holes out at a crucial stage
Timeout! MI need 70 off the last 5 overs. Highly likely that KKR will bowl one more over of spin. The required rate is 14, are we closing in on a thrilling finish here?
Russell to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, bowled full and wide of off, Hardik drives it along the ground wide of cover
Hardik Pandya, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Russell to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught by Ramandeep Singh !! Russell strikes in his first over. Slower short ball dragged wide of off, SKY had to fetch his go-to whippy pull from there and doesn't get the desired connection on it. The fielder at deep square moves across to his right to complete the catch. Suryakumar Yadav c Ramandeep Singh b Russell 11(14) [4s-1]
Russell to Suryakumar Yadav, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Russell to Tilak Varma, leg byes, 1 run, skiddy short of length on middle and leg, Tilak tucks it to the left of square leg. Rolls off the thigh pad...
Russell to Tilak Varma, no run, bumper just outside off, Tilak comes dancing down the wicket looking to slog and gets beaten by the extra bounce
Russell to Tilak Varma, FOUR, I0$ full outside off, Tilak lifts the drive over extra cover and the timing on the shot takes care of the rest. Much-needed boundary for MI...
Russell to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, I0$ back of a length outside off, SKY cuts and gets it to the left of deep cover
Andre Russell, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
MI need 77 from 6 overs. Here's some pace for SKY...
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, quicker on leg stump, worked away to Rinku at deep mid-wicket
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, this one holds up on the surface outside off, SKY mistimes the drive to the left of cover
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, 2 runs, full on leg stump, SKY whips it into the gap to the right of mid-wicket
Chakaravarthy to Tilak Varma, 1 run, full and just outside off, clipped away to the right of deep mid-wicket
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, flatter on the stumps, worked away to the right of deep mid-wicket
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, beaten all ends up. Lands on a fullish length and grips away ever so slightly around off, SKY looks to work leg-side and gets beaten on the outside edge
MI need 82 off 7 overs
Narine to Tilak Varma, no run, pushed full and wide of off, Tilak drives but can't get it past the fielder at extra cover
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, full on leg stump, SKY whips it away to the right of long-on
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, full outside off, SKY gets on the front foot and drives to cover
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, width on offer outside off, SKY sits deep inside the crease and cuts it really late past the diving left hand of backward point
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, quicker and wider of off, SKY looks to cut and gets beaten on the top-edge
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, quicker outside off, SKY punches it off the back foot into the covers
MI need 87 off 8 overs

Chakaravarthy to Tilak Varma, FOUR, and Tilak goes for the switch hit straight away... Gets into position quickly and gets enough contact to get it racing past the fielder at backward point to his right
Tilak Varma, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Chakaravarthy to Rohit, out Caught by Narine!! To be fair, Rohit looked clueless against spin and MI will hope that this (wicket) is a blessing in disguise. After missing our on the reverse/switch hits, Rohit opts for the conventional sweep and gets a thick top-edge that carries straight to the fielder at short fine to his right. No conviction in the shot from Rohit on that occasion. Rohit c Narine b Chakaravarthy 19(24) [4s-1 6s-1]
Chakaravarthy to Rohit, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Chakaravarthy to Rohit, no run, Rohit misses out on the reverse sweep yet again and gets pinged on the pads, appeal for leg before but the impact was well outside off
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, extra bounce on this delivery just outside off, SKY looks to work into the on-side and gets a soft leading edge towards mid-off
Chakaravarthy to Rohit, 1 run, clipped away behind square on the leg-side for a quick single
Chakaravarthy to Rohit, no run, Rohit switches his stance and looks for the swipe over backward point, couldn't get under the dip and gets beaten by the pace. Misses and drags it onto his thigh pad
MI need 93 off 9 overs
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, short outside off, SKY opens the bat face and punches into the off-side
Suryakumar Yadav, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Narine to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Rinku Singh at deep mid-wicket!! Sunil Narine gets his man. He floats the seam-up full delivery on the stumps and draws a slogsweep from Ishan Kishan. Not well timed and the fielder at deep mid-wicket completes a fine catch to his right. Ishan Kishan c Rinku Singh b Narine 40(22) [4s-5 6s-2]
Narine to Ishan Kishan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Narine to Ishan Kishan, no run, Ishan Kishan looks to go for yet another reverse sweep, but ends up getting beaten on the under edge. Gets hit around the thigh pad on the swivel...
Narine to Ishan Kishan, 2 runs, nudged away into the mid-wicket pocket and the duo rush through to complete the second
Narine to Rohit, 1 run, Rohit opts for the reverse sweep and drags it off the thick inside half towards short third. A hurried throw a bit of sloppy work from Salt ends up enabling an easy single
Narine to Rohit, no run, quicker and extra bounce outside off, Rohit cuts and the fielder at short third does well to pull off a diving stop to his right
Timeout. A great powerplay for MI, they're right on track to chase this down. KKR need a couple of wickets to get back into the contest.
Chakaravarthy to Rohit, 1 run, full just outside off, driven out towards sweeper cover, that's the end of the powerplay - a good one for the MI

Chakaravarthy to Rohit, no run, that's a beautiful delivery! Floated up full and just outside off, drifted in nicely and dipped on him as he pressed forward to defend, beat the inside edge and hit his back thigh, UltraEdge confirms no bat, Hawkeye says it would've gone over the stumps, so that's a review lost for KKR now
KKR review. Shout for lbw was turned down, looked like he got some wood on this
Chakaravarthy to Rohit, no run, length delivery just outside off, turns away and bit of extra bounce as Rohit pats it into the leg-side
Chakaravarthy to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, length delivery wide outside off, cut away to sweeper cover off the toe end
Chakaravarthy to Ishan Kishan, no run, full on off-stump from round the wicket, Ishan Kishan eases it towards cover
Chakaravarthy to Rohit, 1 run, length delivery on off-stump, Rohit works it away to deep backward square leg
Varun Chakaravarthy, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack

Highlights (Overs 1-5): -- Vaibhav Arora bowls a quiet opening over -- Starc goes for 11 off his 1st over -- Arora loses radar and concedes 14 off his 2nd over -- Ishan Kishan hits Harshit Rana for 2 fours and a six off his 1st over -- Narine concedes 13 off the last over of the powerplay
Narine to Ishan Kishan, SIX, this goes all the way! Bit of a half-tracker on middle, Ishan Kishan pressed right back and pulled it away over the deep square leg ropes, great finish to the over for MI

Narine to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, bit of innovation! Length delivery outside the leg stump, Ishan Kishan switched up his stance very early to play a switch-hit, didn't switch his hands but hit it well enough to take it to the deep point ropes
Narine to Ishan Kishan, 2 runs, length delivery on leg-stump, heaved away towards deep mid-wicket, couple taken
Narine to Ishan Kishan, no run, length delivery just outside off that turns back into him, was looking to pull and it hit him high on the bat, bounced just short of Starc at mid-on
Narine to Ishan Kishan, no run, full and just outside off, Ishan Kishan looked to drive it through cover and got a thick inside edge onto the pads
Narine to Rohit, 1 run, full on leg-stump, swept away hard but straight to the man at deep backward square leg
Sunil Narine, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Harshit Rana to Ishan Kishan, SIX, into the pads and asking for trouble! Full on middle-leg, easy pickings for Ishan Kishan as he flicked it over the deep mid-wicket fence with the utmost ease
Harshit Rana to Ishan Kishan, wide, length delivery wide outside off, Ishan Kishan reaches out looking to cut and misses, marginal call that
Harshit Rana to Ishan Kishan, no run, length delivery just outside off, punched towards point, good work in the field won't allow a run
Harshit Rana to Ishan Kishan, no run, slower delivery full and outside off from round the wicket, good change of pace and angle, beats him as he looked to cut

Harshit Rana to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, edged and four this time! Length delivery outside off, Ishan Kishan stepped out his crease and threw his bat at this, got a thick outside edge and flew over the man at short third man

Harshit Rana to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, one-bounce four! Just short of length on middle, Ishan Kishan was a little rushed as he short-arm jabbed it up and over mid-wicket, got enough bat and it went one-bounce over the mid-wicket ropes
Harshit Rana to Ishan Kishan, no run, full and outside off, good looking drive goes straight to point
Harshit Rana, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Vaibhav Arora to Rohit, 2 runs, full and shaping in just outside off, Rohit looked to loft this through the line and over mid-off, came off the inner half of the blade and Starc was able to track it down and keep it down to two
Vaibhav Arora to Rohit, no run, full and outside off, Rohit swung for the hills, was looking to go over cow corner and missed it completely!
Vaibhav Arora to Rohit, no run, length delivery wide outside off, was there to be hit and Rohit missed out after flashing at it
Vaibhav Arora to Rohit, no run, good length delivery just outside off, nipped in a touch and caught Rohit on the glove, bit of extra bounce too

Vaibhav Arora to Rohit, SIX, this isn't going well for Vaibhav Arora! A fairly high full-toss on off-stump, Rohit heaved it away over deep square leg, made a clean connection and it sailed over, wasn't given a no-ball for being over waist-high and MI reviewed unsucessfully, so a review lost for MI amidst all that drama!
Vaibhav Arora to Rohit, wide, full and shaping away outside off, past the tramline though so the free-hit stays

Vaibhav Arora to Rohit, no ball, byes, FOUR, oh dear, that's completely slipped out, Vaibhav Arora hurtled this way wide outside off, landed outside the cut-strip and went down to the third man ropes, a no-ball and 4 byes!
Vaibhav Arora to Rohit, no run, full and shaping into the pads, Rohit looked to flick it away and missed after getting beaten on the inside edge, would've gone down leg

Starc to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, beautiful shot! Just back of a length and outside off, Ishan Kishan arched back to create some room before upper-cutting it over the man at short third man, just bounced inside the ropes

Starc to Ishan Kishan, 2 runs, great work in the deep, low full-toss shaping away outside off, Ishan Kishan opened the face of the bat and carved it away fine to the third man ropes, Ramandeep there did well, dived to his right and stopped it
Starc to Rohit, 1 run, full and shaping into middle, knocked towards mid-off for a quick single
Starc to Rohit, no run, good length delivery just outside off, Rohit hangs back looking to cut and gets a bottom-edge that goes to fine-leg
Starc to Rohit, FOUR, nicely struck! Full and shaping into the pads again, Rohit whipped it away to the right of the man at mid-wicket, sweet timing and it raced away
Starc to Rohit, no run, full and shaping into middle, clipped straight to mid-wicket
Mitchell Starc, comes into the attack
Vaibhav Arora to Ishan Kishan, no run, full and outside off, shapes away a lot as Ishan Kishan shoulders arms, probably expected a wide there and didn't get it
Vaibhav Arora to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, that's a good shot! Full and straight on middle, shaped into the pads and Ishan Kishan whipped it up and over mid-wicket for four
Vaibhav Arora to Ishan Kishan, no run, good length delivery slanting across outside off, hint of shape too and Ishan Kishan is beaten on the outside edge
Vaibhav Arora to Rohit, 1 run, full outside off, shapes in prodigiously this time, Rohit bunts it towards mid-on for a single
Vaibhav Arora to Rohit, no run, that's a peach! Full and just outside off, angles in and then shapes away after drawing Rohit into a waft
Vaibhav Arora to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, full on middle, hint of shape away and Ishan Kishan pushes it straight to Starc at mid-on, slight fumble allows a single
Ishan Kishan and Rohit are at the crease. Ishan Kishan is on strike. Vaibhav Arora will open the attack
